    "objective": "Synthesize the relationship between large-scale generation, specific UK transmission voltages, and the technical necessity of high-voltage efficiency.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Large-scale generation feeds the National Grid.",
      "UK transmission voltages are 400 kV, 275 kV, and 132 kV.",
      "High voltage is used to reduce current and minimize I²R heat loss."
    ],
    "questionText": "A new large-scale offshore wind farm is being connected to the UK National Grid to provide power to a city 150 miles away. Explain why the electricity must be stepped up to a specific UK transmission voltage (naming one valid level) for this journey, and how this process prevents excessive energy waste in the long-distance cables.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Identify a valid UK transmission voltage: 400 kV, 275 kV, or 132 kV.",
      "Explain that stepping up the voltage significantly reduces the current (Amps).",
      "State that lower current minimizes heat loss in the cables, known as I²R loss.",
      "Conclude that this high-voltage, low-current approach ensures efficient bulk power delivery over long distances."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about the 'Big Three' transmission voltages. If you increase the voltage to one of these levels, what happens to the current, and how does that stop the cables from wasting energy as heat?"
  }
}

